parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Rack and Pinion Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion assembly can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to navigate turns, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or difficult to turn
the vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
the steering wheel requires excessive turning (up to 45 degrees) to maintain control
the steering wheel ends up in a different position after straightening out
difficulty turning in slight curves.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column assembly can cause the steering column to detach from the assembly, leading to a complete loss of steering control, which can result in accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering column falls off the assembly
loss of steering control
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine electrical system can cause a fire, leading to vehicle damage or total loss, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine check light comes on
fire or sparks are visible near the fuel injection or electrical wires
vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the distributor can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
engine misfires
difficulty starting the engine
engine runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls or dies
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty transmission solenoid can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to slipping, hesitation, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission fluid leaks can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to slipping, hesitation, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks from the transmission pan or lines
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the "check engine" or "transmission" light illuminates on the dashboard
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears.
